<p>The costermongers still further complicate their slang by a mode of multiplication. They thus say, &ldquo;Erth Ewif-gens&rdquo; or <num value="3">3</num> times <num value="5">5</num><hi rend=italics>s.</hi>, which means of course <num value="15">15</num><hi rend=italics>s.</hi>

<p>Speaking of this language, a costermonger said to me: &ldquo;The Irish can&lsquo;t tumble to it anyhow; the Jews can tumble better, but we&lsquo;re <hi rend=italics>their</hi>
masters. Some of the young salesmen at Billingsgate understand us,&mdash;but only at Billingsgate; and they think they&lsquo;re uncommon clever, but they&lsquo;re not quite up to the mark. The police don&lsquo;t understand us at all. It would be a pity if they did.&rdquo; 
