<p>The latter phrase is used when <num value="1">one</num> costermonger warns another of the approach of a policeman &ldquo;who might order him to move on, or be otherwise unpleasant.&rdquo; &ldquo;Cool&rdquo; (look) is exclaimed, or &ldquo;Cool him&rdquo; (look at him). <num value="1">One</num> costermonger told me as a great joke that a very stout policeman, who was then new to the duty, was when in a violent state of perspiration, much offended by a costermonger saying &ldquo;Cool him.&rdquo; 
