<p>This language seems confined, in its general use, to the immediate objects of the costermonger&lsquo;s care; but is, among the more acute members of the fraternity, greatly extended, and is capable of indefinite extension. 
<p>The costermongers oaths, I may conclude, are all in the vernacular; nor are any of the common salutes, such as &ldquo;How d&lsquo;you do?&rdquo; or &ldquo;Good-night&rdquo; known to their slang. 
